### ğŸ“Œ **Confluence Page: Qualtrics Banner Implementation Guide**  

#### ğŸ”¹ **Overview**  
This document provides step-by-step instructions for implementing a **custom banner with text overlay** in **Qualtrics surveys**. The banner dynamically displays location details based on embedded data.  

---

### ğŸ–¼ **Banner Specifications**  
| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| **Width** | 763px |
| **Max Height** | 190px |
| **Text Content** | 1. Curated Experience <br> 2. Colleague Satisfaction Survey <br> 3. Location (from Embedded Data) |
| **Scaling** | Fully responsive (supports up to 400% zoom) |
| **Image Handling** | Ensures full visibility without cropping |

---

### ğŸ›  **Implementation Steps**  

#### 1ï¸âƒ£ **Upload the Banner Image**  
1. Host the banner image on a publicly accessible server or Qualtrics **Graphics Library**.  
2. Copy the image URL for use in the code.  

#### 2ï¸âƒ£ **Add the HTML Code to Qualtrics**  
1. Open **Qualtrics Survey Flow**.  
2. Add a **Descriptive Text** question.  
3. Click **Rich Content Editor â†’ HTML View**.  
4. Paste the following HTML code:  

```html
<div style="width: 100%; max-width: 763px; height: auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; align-items: center; text-align: center; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; padding: 1vh;">
    <img src="YOUR_IMAGE_URL" alt="Banner Image" style="width: 100%; height: auto; max-height: 190px; object-fit: contain;">
    <div style="position: absolute; text-align: center;">
        <h2 style="margin: 0.5vh 0; font-size: 1.8em; color: white; text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);">Curated Experience</h2>
        <h3 style="margin: 0.5vh 0; font-size: 1.5em; color: white; text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);">Colleague Satisfaction Survey</h3>
        <h4 style="margin: 0.5vh 0; font-size: 1.2em; color: #FFD700; text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);">${e://Field/Location}</h4>
    </div>
</div>
```

#### 3ï¸âƒ£ **Replace the Image URL**  
- Replace **YOUR_IMAGE_URL** with the actual hosted image URL.  

#### 4ï¸âƒ£ **Test Responsiveness**  
- Zoom in to **400%** and verify text alignment.  
- Test across **different screen sizes** to ensure proper scaling.  

---

### ğŸ“ **Notes & Considerations**  
- The banner **automatically resizes** to fit different screens.  
- If using a **dark background image**, adjust **text color** for better contrast.  
- The `${e://Field/Location}` placeholder dynamically pulls **location data** from embedded fields.  

---

### ğŸ”„ **Troubleshooting**  
| Issue | Solution |
|-------|----------|
| Image is cropped | Ensure `object-fit: contain` is used in the `<img>` tag. |
| Text alignment issues | Use **relative units** like `em`, `vh`, and `vw` instead of pixels. |
| Embedded data not showing | Verify that `${e://Field/Location}` is properly set in **Survey Flow**. |

---

### âœ… **Final Checklist**  
âœ… Banner image is fully visible without cropping  
âœ… Text is **responsive** and aligns correctly at **400% zoom**  
âœ… **Embedded data** dynamically updates location  

